{{Orphan|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox book | name = ''<big>Five Billion Years of Solitude: The Search for Life Among the Stars</big>'' | image = Five Billion Years of Solitude - bookcover.jpg | caption = First edition cover | author = Lee Billings | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[Science]], [[Astronomy]] | genre = [[Non-Fiction]] | publisher = Current, a member of [[Penguin Group]] | release_date = October 3, 2013 | pages = 304 pp. | media_type = Print, e-book, audiobook | isbn = 978-1617230066 }}
'''''Five Billion Years of Solitude: The Search for Life Among the Stars''''' is a non-fiction work by the science author Lee Billings. The text was initially published on October 3, 2013 by Current.
==Overview== In this book, Billings explores the scientists and science behind the ever-expanding universe of exoplanets. Since the first detection of a planet orbiting another Sun-like star in 1995,<ref>{{cite web|title=The exoplanet next door|url=http://www.nature.com/news/the-exoplanet-next-door-1.11605|location=Nature|year=2012}}</ref> scientists have discovered an increasing number of worlds beyond our solar system through detections by telescopes and spacecraft. Billings reveals the scientists behind these discoveries and their thoughts on not only exoplanets, but also their triumphs and frustrations in their quest to solve one of the greatest mysteries of humankind: Are we alone? Billings includes interviews with [[Frank Drake]], [[Geoffrey Marcy]], Greg Laughlin, [[James Kasting]], [[Matt Mountain]], Wesley Traub, [[Sara Seager]], and many other prominent researchers.
== Topics covered == The book has 10 chapters: * Looking for Longevity * Drake's Orchids * A Fractured Empire * The Worth of a World * After the Gold Rush * The Big Picture * Out of Equilibrium * Aberrations of the Light * The Order of the Null * Into the Barren Lands
== Reviews == * {{Cite news | last = Overbye | first = Dennis | title = Lonely Planet | work = Sunday Book Review | publisher = The New York Times | date = 8 November 2013 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/10/books/review/five-billion-years-of-solitude-by-lee-billings.html | accessdate = 23 November 2013}} * {{Cite news | last = Brown | first = Mike | title = Five Billion Years of Solitude: The Search for Life Among the Stars by Lee Billings | work = WP Opinion | publisher = The Washington Post | date = 15 November 2013 | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/five-billion-years-of-solitude-the-search-for-life-among-the-stars-by-lee-billings/2013/11/15/9f38892c-3684-11e3-be86-6aeaa439845b_story.html | accessdate = 23 November 2013}} * {{Cite news | last = Henderson | first = Caspar | title = Five Billion Years of Solitude: The Search for Life Among the Stars – review | work = | publisher = [[The Guardian]] | date = 21 November 2013 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/books/2013/nov/21/five-billion-years-solitude-lee-billings-review | accessdate = 23 November 2013}} * {{Cite web | last = Teitel| first = Amy Shira | title = Lee Billings' Five Billion Years of Solitude (Review) | work = Discovery News Book Reviews | publisher = Discovery News | date = 14 October 2013 | url = http://news.discovery.com/space/astronomy/lee-billings-five-billion-years-of-solitude-review-131014.htm | accessdate = 23 November 2013}} * {{Cite web | last = Kuchner| first = Marc | title = Five Billion Years of Solitude: The Search for Life Among the Stars | work = Physics Today Volume 67, Issue 12, December 2014 | publisher = AIP Publishing | date = 12 December 2014 | url = http://scitation.aip.org/content/aip/magazine/physicstoday/article/67/12/10.1063/PT.3.2626 | accessdate = 18 December 2014}}
