{{distinguish|Magellanic Stream}} {{Infobox nebula |name = Magellanic Bridge |image = <!-- name only, without File:/Image: and without brackets --> |caption = |credit = |type = H I region |type2 = <!-- can be wikilinked --> |epoch = [[J2000.0]] |subtype = |class = |ra = {{RA|03|11}} |dec = {{DEC|-77.5}} |dist_ly = |dist_pc = |dist_z = |appmag_v = |appdia = <!-- dd°mm'ss".mas --> |size_v = |constellation = |radius_ly = |radius_pc = |dimensions = |absmag_v = |notes = |names = }} The '''Magellanic Bridge''' ('''MBR''')<ref name=SpaceDaily-2014-11-28/> is a stream of neutral [[hydrogen]] that links the two [[Magellanic Clouds]],<ref name=putn> {{cite journal |doi= 10.1071/AS00001 |title= The Magellanic System's Interactive Formations |format= Free PDF download |bibcode= 2000PASA...17....1P |date= 2013 |last1= Putman |first1= M. E. |journal= Publications of the Astronomical Society of Australia |volume= 17 |pages= 1 |url= http://articles.adsabs.harvard.edu/full/2000PASA...17....1P%26data_type%3DPDF_HIGH%26whole_paper%3DYES%26type%3DPRINTER%26filetype%3D.pdf }}</ref> with a few known [[star]]s inside it.<ref name=lehner> Lehner, Nicolas. "[http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2001AAS...199.6506L FUSE Observations of the Magellanic Bridge]." (Abstract) [[American Astronomical Society]], (199th AAS Meeting, #65.06); ''Bulletin of the American Astronomical Society'', Vol. '''33''', p.1408. </ref><ref> Lehner, NNicolas "[https://arxiv.org/pdf/astro-ph/0206250.pdf FUSE Observations of the Magellanic Bridge Gas toward Two Early-Type Stars: Molecules, Physical Conditions, and Relative Abundance]." arXiv preprint astro-ph/0206250 (2002) </ref> It should not be confused with the [[Magellanic Stream]], which links the Magellanic Clouds to the [[Milky Way]]. It was discovered in 1963 by [[J. V. Hindman]] et al.<ref>IOP Science, [http://iopscience.iop.org/0004-637X/658/1/345/fulltext/70633.text.html "The Magellanic Bridge: The Nearest Purely Tidal Stellar Population"], Jason Harris, 2006 October 22, The Astrophysical Journal, 658:345-357, published 2007 March 20</ref>
There is a continuous stream of stars throughout the Bridge linking the [[Large Magellanic Cloud]] (LMC) with the [[Small Magellanic Cloud]] (SMC). This stellar bridge is of greater concentration in the western part. There are two major density clumps, one near the SMC, the other midway between the galaxies, referred to as the ''[[OGLE Island]]''.<ref name=SpaceDaily-2014-11-28>SpaceDaily, [http://www.spacedaily.com/reports/OGLE_ing_the_Magellanic_System_Polish_Astronomers_Discover_Young_Stellar_Bridge_in_the_Magellanic_Clouds_999.html "Polish astronomers spot young Stellar Bridge in the Magellanic Clouds"], 28 November 2014</ref>
